<P>Be&s;eeching the worthy Jacob to pardon her non|payment,
with every kind a&s;&s;urance that her uncle
&s;hould know all his goodne&s;s, &s;he told the po&s;tillion
to take her to Belfont.</P>
<P>He could go no further, he &s;aid, and that but a
