<P>&startq;What a rapid tran&s;ition,&endq; cried he, &startq;was then
mine, from regrets, that robbed life of all charms,
to pro&s;pects which paint it in its mo&s;t viv$d colours
of happine&s;s! from wavering the mo&s;t deplorable,
to re&s;olutions of expiating by a whole life of de|voted
