The partition is thin. I heard my name
&s;poken by Mrs. Tyrold, and the gentle voice of
my Camilla, in accents yet more gentle than even
that voice ever &s;poke before, an&s;wering &s;ome que&s;|tion;
I was not my&s;elf, at fir&s;t, aware of its te|nour
&mdash;but when, unavoidably, I gathered it&mdash;
when I heard words &s;o beautifully harmonizing
with what I had &s;o lately peru&s;ed&mdash;I would in|&s;tantly
have ventured into the room; but Mr.
Tyrold feared &s;urpri&s;ing you&mdash;you went on&mdash;my
fa&s;cinated &s;oul dive&s;ted me of obedience&mdash;of cau|tion&mdash;of
<PB N="341" REF="168">
all but joy and gratitude&mdash;and he could
